                            <comment id="14619398" author="thartmann" created="Thu, 19 Oct 2023 00:04:35 -0700"  >Damon, could you please have a look? Thanks.</comment>
                            <comment id="14619362" author="mseledtsov" created="Wed, 18 Oct 2023 18:45:35 -0700"  >I believe that the failing test should be able to handle configurations with more than one usable page size. Specifically it should be able to handle the period at the end of the output, as JVM is producing such output:&lt;br/&gt;
[0.001s][info][pagesize] Large page support enabled. Usable page sizes: 4k, 2M. Default large page size: 2M.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
My initial investigation is complete. Assigning to Compiler sub-component to investigate the test, since the test belongs to JVM Compiler. It is possible also this could be a JVM bug, in which case this could be further reassigned.</comment>
